<p>cassandra cluster - [cqlsh 4.1.1 | Cassandra 2.0.14.348 | CQL spec 3.1.1 | Thrift protocol 19.39.0]</p>  <p>client program: .NET 3.5, <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/cassandra-sharp/0.6.4" rel="nofollow">cassandra-sharp 0.6.4</a></p>  <p>table in cassandra db: applications  <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/sGTuE.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/sGTuE.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <pre><code>public void GetApplications()     {         using (ICluster cluster = ClusterManager.GetCluster("CassandraCluster"))         {             //string q = "select * from applications where team_id = 3c942256-5c04-463b-9e41-df8d8f43b5cf";             //string q = "select * from applications where team_id = '3c942256-5c04-463b-9e41-df8d8f43b5cf'";              byte[] teamid = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes("3c942256-5c04-463b-9e41-df8d8f43b5cf");             string q = "select * from applications where team_id = blobAsUuid(teamid)";              var result = cluster.ExecuteCql(q);          }          ClusterManager.Shutdown();     } </code></pre>  <p>formed query in multiple ways but no luck. used UUID in where clause without quotes around it, placed that UUID within quotes, used blobAsUuid function.</p>  <p>error when uuid is used with &amp; without quotes <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/juTdc.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/juTdc.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>error when blobAsUuid function is used <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/gyDT7.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/gyDT7.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>